Time Table

Daily Schedule /Daily Routine

(Monday - Friday):

TimeActivity

7:00 AM – 7:30 AM -- Wake up & morning routine (freshen up).
7:30 AM – 8:00 AM -- Light exercise,stretching ,walk and preparation for the day.
8:00 AM – 8:30 AM --  Breakfast and review the day's learning goals.
8:30 AM – 9:00 AM -- Quick revision / Front-end development study (review previous concepts, quick practice).
9:00 AM – 12:00 PM -- English-speaking class.
12:00 PM – 12:30 PM -- Break (relax, social media, short walk)
12:30 PM - 1:00 PM --  Lunch break and short relaxation.
1:00 PM – 2:30 PM -- Front-End Development Learning (learning new concepts, Theory & Watching  Tutorials)
2:30 PM – 4:00 PM -- Hands-on coding & small exercises
4:00 PM – 4:30 PM -- Tea/snack break & light relaxation
4:30 PM – 6:00 PM -- Coding practice (building projects, solving coding challenges) / Project Work (HTML, CSS, JavaScript, React projects)
6:00 PM – 8:00 PM -- Gym, Outdoor walk or any physical activity.
8:00 PM – 9:00 PM -- Dinner & family time
9:00 PM – 9:30 PM -- Review of the day's learning, note-taking, and planning for the next day / GitHub work, debugging, revising concepts / Final coding practice or review. 
9:30 PM – 10:00 PM -- Portfolio building, watching tutorials, or interview prep
10:00 PM - 10:30 PM -- Personal time, light reading, or relaxation.
10:30 PM – 11:00 PM -- Prepare for sleep / Wind down (read, relax, light entertainment)
11:00 PM -- Sleep.!



Weekend Schedule (Saturday & Sunday):
7:00 AM - 7:300 AM: Wake up, , morning routine, 
7:30 AM – 8:30 AM -- light exercise .
8:30 AM – 9:00 AM --  Breakfast.
9:00 AM - 12:00 PM: , 
9:30 AM – 12:30 PM -- Extended coding practice , Major project work (React, JavaScript, API integration) project work, or portfolio development.
12:00 PM - 1:00 PM: Lunch break.
1:30 PM – 2:00 PMDebugging, testing, and deploying projects
2:00 PM - 4:00 PM: Framework learning (React/Vue/Angular), advanced JavaScript concepts, or Git/GitHub practice.
4:00 PM – 5:00 PMMock interviews, problem-solving, and online coding challenges
5:00 PM - 6:00 PM: Continue project work, portfolio building, or explore new front-end technologies.
6:00 PM – 7:00 PMFree time (relax, go out, watch something)
7:00 PM – 8:00 PM Review learning, plan the upcoming week, or work on portfolio, Final portfolio updates & documentation
8:00 PM - 9:00 PM: Dinner break.
9:00 PM – 10:00 PMSocial/family time or light study , Personal time, relaxation, or light reading.
10:00 PM – 11:00 PMWind down & Prepare for sleep.
11:00 PM: Sleep.



Weekly Focus Breakdown within the Timetable:
Week 1 (HTML & CSS Fundamentals):
Allocate the 1-3pm and 3-6pm time slots for learning HTML and CSS.
Use weekend time for building basic layouts and portfolio page planning.

Week 2 (JavaScript Fundamentals):
Dedicate the 1-3pm and 3-6pm time slots to JavaScript learning and DOM manipulation.
Use weekend time to build the interactive projects.

Week 3 (Intermediate JavaScript & Version Control):
1-3pm advanced JavaScript and 3-6pm git and github practice.
Use weekend time to build the single page application, and practice git.

Week 4 (Frameworks & Portfolio Building):
1-3pm framework learning and 3-6pm portfolio building.
Use the weekend for framework learning, and portfolio building.

Important Considerations:
Flexibility: This is a guideline. Adjust it based on your energy levels and learning pace.
Breaks: Take short breaks during study sessions to avoid burnout.
Food and Hydration: Eat healthy meals and stay hydrated.
Sleep: Aim for 7-8 hours of sleep each night.
Review: Regularly review your notes and practice previous concepts.
Active Learning: Don't just watch tutorials. Code along and experiment.
Problem-Solving: When you encounter errors, try to solve them yourself. Use online resources and communities.
Portfolio: Start building your portfolio early and update it regularly.
Apply for jobs: During the last week start applying for jobs.

This structured timetable will help you stay organized and focused on your front-end developer journey. Remember to be patient and persistent, and you'll achieve your goals.

This schedule ensures consistent learning while keeping a balance between English improvement, front-end development, physical health, and relaxation.






